                .iq-card
                    .iq-card-header.d-flex.justify-content-between
                        .iq-header-title
                            h4.card-title Equal-width
                    .iq-card-body
                        p
                            | For example, here are two grid layouts that apply to every device and viewport, from
                            code xs
                            |  to
                            code xl
                            | . Add any number of unit-less classes for each breakpoint you need and every column will be the same width.
                        .iq-example-row
                            .container-fluid
                                // Stack the columns on mobile by making one full-width and the other half-width
                                .row.mb-3
                                    .col-12.col-md-8 .col-12 .col-md-8
                                    .col-6.col-md-4 .col-6 .col-md-4
                                // Columns start at 50% wide on mobile and bump up to 33.3% wide on desktop
                                .row.mb-3
                                    .col-6.col-md-4 .col-6 .col-md-4
                                    .col-6.col-md-4 .col-6 .col-md-4
                                    .col-6.col-md-4 .col-6 .col-md-4
                                // Columns are always 50% wide, on mobile and desktop
                                .row
                                    .col-6 .col-6
                                    .col-6 .col-6
                .iq-card
                    .iq-card-header.d-flex.justify-content-between
                        .iq-header-title
                            h4.card-title Setting one column width
                    .iq-card-body
                        p
                            | Auto-layout for flexbox grid columns also means you can set the width of one column and have the sibling columns automatically resize around it. You may use predefined grid classes (as shown below), grid mixins, or inline widths. Note that the other columns will resize no matter the width of the center column.
                        .iq-example-row
                            .container-fluid
                                .row.mb-3
                                    .col
                                        | 1 of 3
                                    .col-6
                                        | 2 of 3 (wider)
                                    .col
                                        | 3 of 3
                                .row
                                    .col
                                        | 1 of 3
                                    .col-5
                                        | 2 of 3 (wider)
                                    .col
                                        | 3 of 3
                .iq-card
                    .iq-card-header.d-flex.justify-content-between
                        .iq-header-title
                            h4.card-title Variable width content
                    .iq-card-body
                        p
                            | Use
                            code col-{breakpoint}-auto
                            |  classes to size columns based on the natural width of their content.
                        .iq-example-row
                            .container-fluid
                                .row.justify-content-md-center.mb-3
                                    .col.col-lg-2
                                        | 1 of 3
                                    .col-md-auto
                                        | Variable width content
                                    .col.col-lg-2
                                        | 3 of 3
                                .row
                                    .col
                                        | 1 of 3
                                    .col-md-auto
                                        | Variable width content
                                    .col.col-lg-2
                                        | 3 of 3
                .iq-card
                    .iq-card-header.d-flex.justify-content-between
                        .iq-header-title
                            h4.card-title Equal-width multi-row
                    .iq-card-body
                        p
                            | Create equal-width columns that span multiple rows by inserting a
                            code .w-100
                            |  where you want the columns to break to a new line. Make the breaks responsive by mixing the
                            code .w-100
                            |  with some
                            a(href='https://getbootstrap.com/' target='_blank') responsive display utilities
                            | .
                        .iq-example-row
                            .container-fluid
                                .row
                                    .col col
                                    .col col
                                    .w-100
                                    .col col
                                    .col col
                .iq-card
                    .iq-card-header.d-flex.justify-content-between
                        .iq-header-title
                            h4.card-title Responsive classes
                    .iq-card-body
                        p
                            | Bootstrap&rsquo;s grid includes five tiers of predefined classes for building complex responsive layouts. Customize the size of your columns on extra small, small, medium, large, or extra large devices however you see fit.
                        h4.card-title All breakpoints
                        p
                            | For grids that are the same from the smallest of devices to the largest, use the
                            code .col
                            |  and
                            code .col-*
                            |  classes. Specify a numbered class when you need a particularly sized column; otherwise, feel free to stick to
                            code .col
                            | .
                        .iq-example-row
                            .container-fluid
                                .row.mb-3
                                    .col col
                                    .col col
                                    .col col
                                    .col col
                                .row
                                    .col-8 col-8
                                    .col-4 col-4
                .iq-card
                    .iq-card-header.d-flex.justify-content-between
                        .iq-header-title
                            h4.card-title Stacked to horizontal
                    .iq-card-body
                        p
                            | Using a single set of
                            code .col-sm-*
                            |  classes, you can create a basic grid system that starts out stacked and becomes horizontal at the small breakpoint (
                            code sm
                            | ).
                        .iq-example-row
                            .container-fluid
                                .row.mb-3
                                    .col-sm-8 col-sm-8
                                    .col-sm-4 col-sm-4
                                .row
                                    .col-sm col-sm
                                    .col-sm col-sm
                                    .col-sm col-sm
                .iq-card
                    .iq-card-header.d-flex.justify-content-between
                        .iq-header-title
                            h4.card-title Mix and match
                    .iq-card-body
                        p
                            | Don&rsquo;t want your columns to simply stack in some grid tiers? Use a combination of different classes for each tier as needed. See the example below for a better idea of how it all works.
                        .iq-example-row
                            .container-fluid
                                // Stack the columns on mobile by making one full-width and the other half-width
                                .row.mb-3
                                    .col-12.col-md-8 .col-12 .col-md-8
                                    .col-6.col-md-4 .col-6 .col-md-4
                                // Columns start at 50% wide on mobile and bump up to 33.3% wide on desktop
                                .row.mb-3
                                    .col-6.col-md-4 .col-6 .col-md-4
                                    .col-6.col-md-4 .col-6 .col-md-4
                                    .col-6.col-md-4 .col-6 .col-md-4
                                // Columns are always 50% wide, on mobile and desktop
                                .row
                                    .col-6 .col-6
                                    .col-6 .col-6
                .iq-card
                    .iq-card-header.d-flex.justify-content-between
                        .iq-header-title
                            h4.card-title Gutters
                    .iq-card-body
                        p
                            | Gutters can be responsively adjusted by breakpoint-specific padding and negative margin utility classes. To change the gutters in a given row, pair a negative margin utility on the
                            code .row
                            |  and matching padding utilities on the
                            code .col
                            | s. The
                            code .container
                            |  or
                            code .container-fluid
                            |  parent may need to be adjusted too to avoid unwanted overflow, using again matching padding utility.
                        p
                            | Here&rsquo;s an example of customizing the Bootstrap grid at the large (
                            code lg
                            | ) breakpoint and above. We&rsquo;ve increased the
                            code .col
                            |  padding with
                            code .px-lg-5
                            | , counteracted that with
                            code .mx-lg-n5
                            |  on the parent
                            code .row
                            |  and then adjusted the
                            code .container
                            |  wrapper with
                            code .px-lg-5
                            | .
                        .iq-example-row
                            .container-fluid.px-lg-5
                                .row.mx-lg-n5
                                    .col.py-3.px-lg-5.border.bg-light Custom column padding
                                    .col.py-3.px-lg-5.border.bg-light Custom column padding
